Rating: 4
It's rare that my grocery store has good looking watercress, but one day it did, so I bought several bunches, but had no idea what I was going to do with them. I found this recipe and tried it. Sooo good! I love the exotic flavors! I didn't have any bell peppers on hand, so I french cut green beans and steamed them and tossed them with the dressing. So healthy and delicious. Will definately make again and again. For the rest of the watercress I had on hand, I did PANFRIED TOFU ON SESAME WATERCRESS WITH SOY-ORANGE DRESSING also on this web site and also very, very tasty!

